  "prompt": "Are there legal obligations for financial institutions regarding money laundering?",
  "response": "Financial institutions have significant legal obligations to prevent money laundering, including:\n\n1. Compliance Requirements\n- Implementing anti-money laundering (AML) programs\n- Conducting customer due diligence\n- Reporting suspicious transactions\n- Maintaining transaction records\n\n2. Regulatory Reporting\n- Filing suspicious activity reports (SARs)\n- Submitting currency transaction reports\n- Identifying and verifying customer identities\n\n3. Risk Assessment\n- Conducting ongoing risk assessments\n- Monitoring high-risk transactions\n- Implementing internal controls\n\n4. Legal Frameworks\n- Following Bank Secrecy Act requirements\n- Adhering to international anti-money laundering standards\n- Complying with Know Your Customer (KYC) regulations\n\n5. Potential Penalties\n- Significant financial fines\n- Potential criminal prosecution\n- Loss of banking licenses\n\nThese obligations aim to prevent criminal financial activities and protect the financial system's integrity.\n\nWould you like me to elaborate on any of these specific aspects of money laundering regulations?",
